## Link to this sectionUsage#

To train a YOLO26n-sem model on the ADE20K dataset for 100 [epochs](https://www.ultralytics.com/glossary/epoch) with an image size of 512, you can use the following code snippets. For a comprehensive list of available arguments, refer to the model [Training](/modes/train) page.

Train Example
    
    
    from ultralytics import YOLO
    
    # Load a model
    model = YOLO("yolo26n-sem.pt")  # load a pretrained model (recommended for training)
    
    # Train the model
    results = model.train(data="ade20k.yaml", epochs=100, imgsz=512)

